         <td id="content"> 
          <table border="0px" cellspacing="0px" cellpadding="0px"> 
           <tbody>
            <tr> 
             <td class="home_middle"> <img src="/mediation/include_images/deal.jpg" width="441" height="282" hspace="0" vspace="0" border="0"> 
              <div class="middle_bottom"> 
               <p>Welcome to the <strong>New Jersey State Board of Mediation (NJSBM)</strong> website. As you review our homepage, you will see a number of options from which to choose. These selections will provide you with valuable information about the <strong>NJSBM's</strong> services, laws and rules governing the Board functions. This site provides links to other state and federal sites that address related labor relations and workplace issues.</p> 
              </div> </td> 
             <td class="home_right" valign="top"> 
              <div class="right_top"></div><img src="/mediation/include_images/top_round.jpg" width="222" height="13" hspace="0" vspace="0" border="0">
              <div class="what_we_do">
                WHAT WE DO 
              </div> 
              <div class="right_bottom"> 
               <img src="/mediation/include_images/hand_shake.jpg" width="210" height="83" hspace="0" vspace="0" border="0" class="hand_shake">
               <br> 
               <p>The <strong>NJSBM</strong> was established by statue in 1941, the New Jersey Employer-Employee Relations Act, as an independent agency housed within the Department of Labor and Workforce Development. The Board's primary mission is the prevention or prompt settlement of labor disputes involving private sector employers, private employees, and unions that represent private employees and to promote labor and management harmony and peace. Occasionally, the Board addresses labor relation disputes of public sector employers not covered by the Public Employment Relations Commission.</p> 
              </div> </td> 
            </tr> 
